## forEachDict() function

Iterate over a dictionary, invoking a callback for each non-undefined value

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
export declare function forEachDict<T>(input: Dict<T>, callback: (value: T, key: string, dict: Dict<T>) => void): void;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  input | Dict&lt;T&gt; | Dictionary to iterate over |
|  callback | (value: T, key: string, dict: Dict&lt;T&gt;) =&gt; void | Callback to invoke for each value |

<b>Returns:</b>

void
